"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody. The cells in your body are defined by their DNA. What makes up a blood cell or a bone cell or a skin cell is the combination of DNA that is kind of set in stone, and there can be small amounts of variation in this, but for the most part it stays what it is. Your gut is made up of bacteria and archaea and what's broadly called procreatic life that transfers DNA across the cell membrane. These don't have nucleuses that contain and protect the DNA. They actually transfer DNA based on their circumstances, so they literally morph from one type of bacteria or archaea into another type based on circumstances, based on calories, based on what you're eating. And so this is very, very unique. It's very dynamic, and your gut is constantly changing. It needs to stay up to date. That's why you need to eat a diverse group of living foods so that your gut can be as healthy as it can possibly be. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.48,\n      \"end\": 1.76,\n      \"duration\": 1.28,\n      \"confidence\": 0.991,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.36,\n          \"end\": 1.52,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 1.52,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.957\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    